data.enText: to make an exact copy of sth

data.chText: （尤指不必要时）重复，再做一次
data.enText: to do sth again, especially when it is unnecessary

data.chText: 重复别人已经做过的工作毫无意义。
data.enText: There's no point in duplicating work already done.

data.chText: 完全一样的；复制的；副本的
data.enText: exactly like sth else; made as a copy of sth else

data.chText: 完全一样的东西；复制品；副本
data.enText: one of two or more things that are the same in every detail
Is this a duplicate or the original?
as two copies that are exactly the same in every detail

data.chText: 准备一个一式两份的合同
data.enText: to prepare a contract in duplicate

simple_means.memory_skill: du 二，双 + plic 重复 + ate 使… → 重复第二份 → 复制

means: (尤指不必要时)重复，再做一次

ex.chText: 他保留下原件而只给了她一份复印件。
ex.enText: He kept the original copy and gave her only a Xerox.

ex.chText: 我可以复印一些微缩胶片上的资料吗？
ex.enText: Can I get a Xerox of some material on the microfilm?

synonyms.bx: 首字母通常大写，指用“施乐”静电复印机印出的文件或图像。

ex.chText: 她给他们寄去了她美国护照的复印件。
ex.enText: She forwarded them a copy of her American passport.

ex.chText: 一定要把所有文件都复印好副本。
ex.enText: Be sure to make copies of all the papers.

ex.chText: 这不是真正的都铎时期的桌子，但却是很逼真的仿制品。
ex.enText: It is not a genuine Tudor table, but it's an excellent copy.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，尤指文件或艺术品的复制件。

ex.chText: 大部分钥匙锁匠都能配。
ex.enText: Locksmiths can make duplicates of most keys.

ex.chText: 他把复印件和原件都保留着。
ex.enText: He kept both the duplicate and the copy.

synonyms.bx: 指与原件毫无二致的复制品，含可替代原件之意。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：复制品，复印件

data.enText: as two copies that are exactly the same in every detail

data.chText: 准备一个一式两份的合同
data.enText: to prepare a contract in duplicate

tr: a copy that corresponds to an original exactly
example: he made a duplicate for the files

tr: something additional of the same kind
example: he always carried extras in case of an emergency

tr: make or do or perform again
example: He could never replicate his brilliant performance of the magic trick

tr: make a duplicate or duplicates of
example: Could you please duplicate this letter for me?
The polished surface twinned his face and chest in reverse

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /'djuːplɪkeɪt, am 'duː-/. The noun and adjective are pronounced /'djuːplɪkət, am 'duː-/. 动词读作 /'djuːplɪkeɪt, 美 'duː-/,名词和形容词读作 /'djuːplɪkət, 美 'duː-/。

value.def: If you duplicate something that has already been done, you repeat or copy it.

example.ex: His task will be to duplicate his success overseas here at home...
example.tran: 他在海外取得了成功，现在的任务就是要在国内再创辉煌。

example.ex: Scientists hope the work done in collaboration with other researchers may be duplicated elsewhere.
example.tran: 科学家们希望与其他研究人员合作的成果可以适用于别处。

example.ex: Charles scored again, with an exact duplicate of his first goal.
example.tran: 查尔斯梅开二度,与第一次破门如出一辙。

value.def: To duplicate something which has been written, drawn, or recorded onto tape means to make exact copies of it.

example.ex: She found Ned alone in the photocopy room, duplicating some articles.
example.tran: 她发现内德一个人在复印室里复印一些文章。

example.ex: ...a business which duplicates video and cinema tapes for the movie makers.
example.tran: 为电影制片商复制录像带和影带的行业

example.ex: I'm on my way to Switzerland, but I've lost my card. I've got to get a duplicate.
example.tran: 我正在去瑞士的路上,可是我把卡弄丢了，得去补办一张。

value.def: Duplicate is used to describe things that have been made as an exact copy of other things, usually in order to serve the same purpose.

example.ex: He let himself in with a duplicate key.
example.tran: 他用一把复制的钥匙打开门进去。

example.ex: ...a duplicate copy of the loan contract.

value.tran: 完全一样的;复制的;副本的
